story as Indicator of Swiss Secondary School Art Education History: A Case Study of the Canton of Bern from 1994 to Today -- tA Tool for Art Educators: The Common European Framework of Reference for Visual Literacy -- tPlayful Hands-on Crafting for Personal Growth and Communal Well-being -- tTeaching Empathy for Dementia by Arts-based Methods -- tPotential of Aesthetic Experiences in the Field of Teacher Education -- t#4 Identities -- tImperatives for Design Education in Places Other Than Europe or North America! -- tThe Design Laboratory. A Paradigm for Design Education? -- tThe Joys and Obstacles of a Change Agent: Teaching in Pakistan’s Only Postgraduate Program in Art Education -- tMestiza Pedagogies: Subversive Cartography Applied to Arts and Crafts Making -- tWar on Cash -- tHyper-listening: Praxis -- tInSea Regional Conference Vienna0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aDie Kunstpädagogik und Kunstvermittlung waren stets mit gesellschaftlichen und sozialen Veränderungen konfrontiert. Aktuell stehen wir vor historischen Herausforderungen und Phänomenen, mit denen wir nie gerechnet hätten: die globale Finanzkrise, die massiven Migrationsströme und die Durchdringung des Alltags mit neuen Technologien. Kreative Kompetenzen sind notwendig, um disziplinäre Grenzen zu überwinden und in einer diversen Gesellschaft gleiche Chancen auf Bildung zu ermöglichen. Die Publikation diskutiert kritisch die Rolle von Kunst- und Designvermittlung inmitten dieses gesellschaftlichen Wandels – anhand von theoretischen Reflexionen, praktischen Erfahrungen und empirischen Analysen.  aIt has always been the case that the teaching of art has had to deal with social changes. We are currently facing historic challenges and phenomena which we could never have imagined – the global financial crisis, the massive migration flows, and the ubiquitous spread of new technologies in our everyday life. Creative competence is needed for overcoming the disciplinary boundaries and in order to make equal opportunities for education possible in a diverse society. This publication takes a critical look at the role of art and design education amidst these social changes – using theoretical reflection, practical experience, and empirical analysis.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aArtxCongressesxStudy and teaching (Higher)xConference papers and proceedings. 0aArtxStudy and teaching (Higher)vCongresses. 0aDesignxStudy and teaching (Higher)vCongresses. 4aDigitalisierung. 4aKunst- und Designvermittlung. 4aKünstlerische Forschung. 4aMigration. 4aMuseum /Sozialer Wandel. 7aART / General.2bisacsh1 aBast, Gerald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChattopadhyay, Budhaditya, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCoutts, Glen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDesai, Dipti, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDodd, Jocelyn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEngel, Birgit, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEça, Teresa Torres de, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGielen, Pascal, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGregory, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHamlin, Jessica, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHann, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHasenhütl, Gert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaslam, Susannah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHossain, Annika, econtributor.4ctb